1
00:01:38,980 --> 00:01:41,780
[Episode 6]

2
00:01:46,360 --> 00:01:48,600
Xing Wu.

3
00:01:48,600 --> 00:01:51,073
I have some good news.

4
00:01:51,073 --> 00:01:53,060
I'm going back to Beijing.

5
00:02:03,558 --> 00:02:07,038
Congratulations.
You can finally leave Zhazhating.

6
00:02:07,038 --> 00:02:08,799
Same to you.

7
00:02:08,799 --> 00:02:12,106
Finally, you don't have to
put up with me anymore.

8
00:02:31,959 --> 00:02:34,273
- It's here.
- Yeah.

9
00:02:42,919 --> 00:02:45,740
The pickup is here. Let's go.

10
00:02:46,718 --> 00:02:49,039
We're taking this? Quite a grand send-off.

11
00:02:49,039 --> 00:02:51,598
It's faster than a three-wheeler
and more spacious than an SUV.

12
00:02:51,598 --> 00:02:53,759
Fuzz's dad lent it to us.

13
00:02:53,759 --> 00:02:56,926
It's the best treatment in Zhazhating.

14
00:03:00,079 --> 00:03:03,200
Auntie, Grandma, I'm leaving now.

15
00:03:03,200 --> 00:03:05,319
If you have no one to eat with,

16
00:03:05,319 --> 00:03:07,320
you can video call me.

17
00:03:07,320 --> 00:03:10,598
Okay. Study hard when you get back.

18
00:03:10,598 --> 00:03:12,799
Don't worry about us.

19
00:03:13,398 --> 00:03:17,998
Ye, if there was anything
I didn't do well during your stay,

20
00:03:17,998 --> 00:03:20,398
please forgive me.

21
00:03:20,398 --> 00:03:22,079
Look at how great you are.

22
00:03:22,079 --> 00:03:24,359
You're going to study abroad soon.

23
00:03:24,359 --> 00:03:28,118
I won't pretend to want you to stay.

24
00:03:28,118 --> 00:03:30,466
That would only hold you back.

25
00:03:31,118 --> 00:03:32,398
Don't worry, Auntie.

26
00:03:32,398 --> 00:03:34,806
I'll pay the balance.

27
00:03:35,598 --> 00:03:38,359
Well... It's not that.

28
00:03:38,359 --> 00:03:40,678
It was my duty to take care of you.

29
00:03:40,678 --> 00:03:43,079
I didn't do it just for the money.

30
00:03:43,079 --> 00:03:44,878
Besides, you didn't stay the full term.

31
00:03:44,878 --> 00:03:47,600
You must not pay me the balance.

32
00:03:47,600 --> 00:03:49,639
Don't you dare send it to me.

33
00:03:49,639 --> 00:03:52,906
I definitely will. Uncle Sun will contact you.

34
00:03:56,558 --> 00:03:59,239
Cousin!

35
00:03:59,239 --> 00:04:01,039
Cousin!

36
00:04:01,039 --> 00:04:03,239
- Here.
- What's this?

37
00:04:03,239 --> 00:04:05,718
Fruit. Not cheap knock-offs this time.

38
00:04:05,718 --> 00:04:09,878
They're really imported avocados and cherries.
Take them for the road.

39
00:04:09,878 --> 00:04:11,319
And these are from my mom.

40
00:04:11,319 --> 00:04:14,759
All your favorites. Eat them if you get hungry.

41
00:04:14,759 --> 00:04:16,999
- Well...
- Just take it.

42
00:04:16,999 --> 00:04:18,918
- Take it.
- It's quite heavy.

43
00:04:18,918 --> 00:04:20,918
- Here, I'll take it.
- Let me.

44
00:04:20,918 --> 00:04:25,838
It's a journey of several hours.
You'll get hungry, and you'll need it.

45
00:04:25,838 --> 00:04:27,798
- Thanks, then.
- We should go.

46
00:04:27,798 --> 00:04:29,319
- We're leaving now.
- Okay.

47
00:04:29,319 --> 00:04:31,478
- We're off.
- Take care.

48
00:04:31,478 --> 00:04:33,199
- Bye, Qing Ye!
- Have a safe trip.

49
00:04:33,199 --> 00:04:35,025
Right.

50
00:04:35,025 --> 00:04:36,126
Go.

51
00:04:36,126 --> 00:04:37,319
- We're off.
- Bye-bye.

52
00:04:37,319 --> 00:04:39,280
- Bye!
- Bye, Auntie, Grandma!

53
00:04:39,280 --> 00:04:40,348
- Bye-bye!
- Bye!

54
00:04:40,348 --> 00:04:42,426
Take it slow!

55
00:04:54,519 --> 00:04:56,893
Sir, please stop for a moment.

56
00:05:01,398 --> 00:05:03,773
I want to take another look.

57
00:05:31,240 --> 00:05:34,499
It reminds me of when we first met.

58
00:05:43,320 --> 00:05:45,598
<i>Hello, beautiful.</i>

59
00:05:45,598 --> 00:05:47,366
<i>Nuts.</i>

60
00:05:50,319 --> 00:05:52,133
You're quite good at swearing.

61
00:05:54,238 --> 00:05:55,879
I'm about to leave.

62
00:05:55,879 --> 00:05:58,179
Can't you say something nice?

63
00:05:59,999 --> 00:06:01,826
I'm just telling the truth.

64
00:06:09,319 --> 00:06:12,879
If I remember correctly,
it was on this very road back then.

65
00:06:12,879 --> 00:06:16,840
You must have been calling me
a country bumpkin in your head.

66
00:06:18,319 --> 00:06:22,200
I wasn't. I was calling you a jerk.

67
00:06:24,199 --> 00:06:27,786
Then my first impression of you
was quite accurate.

68
00:06:32,560 --> 00:06:34,798
Everyone else had something to say.

69
00:06:34,798 --> 00:06:37,273
Don't you want to say anything to me?

70
00:06:50,720 --> 00:06:52,513
Say what?

71
00:06:54,079 --> 00:06:57,478
There's a good chance
I'll never come back to Zhazhating.

72
00:06:57,478 --> 00:07:01,240
As a farewell,
you should at least say something.

73
00:07:04,639 --> 00:07:08,353
Beijing isn't that far. What's there to say?

74
00:07:09,759 --> 00:07:12,959
I thought you'd at least say,

75
00:07:12,959 --> 00:07:15,039
"Hope to see you again."

76
00:07:17,559 --> 00:07:20,886
You probably don't want to see me
or Zhazhating ever again.

77
00:07:24,398 --> 00:07:26,029
That's true.

78
00:07:28,040 --> 00:07:29,838
When you first arrived,

79
00:07:29,838 --> 00:07:32,893
you must have been utterly disappointed
with everything here.

80
00:07:34,119 --> 00:07:36,586
I felt like my life was over.

81
00:07:37,280 --> 00:07:41,519
You practically had the word "disgust"
written all over your face.

82
00:07:41,519 --> 00:07:43,038
Was it that obvious?

83
00:07:43,038 --> 00:07:45,531
Like a startled cat,

84
00:07:45,531 --> 00:07:48,020
your fur was bristling from head to toe.

85
00:07:49,478 --> 00:07:51,718
If that's the case,

86
00:07:51,718 --> 00:07:53,960
you were paying quite close attention.

87
00:08:09,240 --> 00:08:11,506
- Pull over.
- Okay.

88
00:08:29,398 --> 00:08:33,000
I didn't realize
lavender looks so beautiful up close.

89
00:08:33,720 --> 00:08:37,266
These little flowers are so purple.
They're really pretty.

90
00:08:37,919 --> 00:08:41,133
Are they? It's not your first time here.

91
00:08:43,199 --> 00:08:45,758
Right. They're not just pretty.

92
00:08:45,758 --> 00:08:47,959
They can cool you down and clear toxins,

93
00:08:47,959 --> 00:08:49,319
relieve wind and stop itching.

94
00:08:49,319 --> 00:08:53,079
They can be made into
tea bags and essential oils which can...

95
00:08:53,079 --> 00:08:55,638
<i>Can calm the mind and relieve anxiety.</i>

96
00:08:55,638 --> 00:08:58,838
Calm the mind and relieve anxiety.

97
00:08:58,838 --> 00:09:01,566
- Good memory.
- Of course.

98
00:09:07,838 --> 00:09:11,780
I'm leaving soon. Take a picture of me here.

99
00:10:05,638 --> 00:10:06,920
Did you take it or not?

100
00:10:06,920 --> 00:10:08,758
What are you laughing at?

101
00:10:08,758 --> 00:10:11,000
I'm taking it. I am.

102
00:10:24,319 --> 00:10:25,679
By the way...

103
00:10:25,679 --> 00:10:27,126
Cousin.

104
00:10:28,598 --> 00:10:30,279
I'm leaving anyway.

105
00:10:30,279 --> 00:10:32,460
Let's take a photo together.

106
00:10:34,399 --> 00:10:36,273
I don't look good in photos.

107
00:10:37,039 --> 00:10:38,238
Save it as a memento, okay?

108
00:10:38,238 --> 00:10:40,180
Hurry up.

109
00:10:48,679 --> 00:10:51,060
Smile, will you?

110
00:10:55,118 --> 00:10:57,809
Three, two, one.

111
00:11:04,065 --> 00:11:06,600
<i>I thought I was at a dead end,</i>

112
00:11:06,600 --> 00:11:10,825
<i>yet Zhazhating has become my warm harbor.</i>

113
00:11:10,825 --> 00:11:13,159
<i>Every breath of sea breeze here</i>

114
00:11:13,159 --> 00:11:16,175
<i>carries the most genuine look of life,</i>

115
00:11:16,175 --> 00:11:19,060
<i>giving me the strength to start over.</i>

116
00:11:40,399 --> 00:11:42,440
Go on.

117
00:11:42,440 --> 00:11:44,440
Thank you.

118
00:11:44,440 --> 00:11:46,325
Have a nice trip.

119
00:11:47,640 --> 00:11:49,240
Let's...

120
00:11:49,240 --> 00:11:50,762
have a hug.

121
00:12:12,600 --> 00:12:14,679
You're never this polite.

122
00:12:14,679 --> 00:12:16,400
It feels a little weird.

123
00:12:16,400 --> 00:12:19,353
It's fine. You won't have to.

124
00:12:20,600 --> 00:12:21,840
The contract has expired.

125
00:12:21,840 --> 00:12:23,512
It's void now.

126
00:12:24,360 --> 00:12:25,700
Goodbye.

127
00:13:12,840 --> 00:13:14,840
<i>Beijing, I'm back!</i>

128
00:13:14,840 --> 00:13:16,562
<i>Wait for me, guys.</i>

129
00:13:37,120 --> 00:13:40,912
How come you even recorded a video?

130
00:14:10,466 --> 00:14:11,600
<i>I'm here.</i>

131
00:14:11,600 --> 00:14:13,159
<i>Should I go straight to your place,</i>

132
00:14:13,159 --> 00:14:15,820
<i>or should we grab a meal first?</i>

133
00:14:38,440 --> 00:14:39,559
Hello?

134
00:14:39,559 --> 00:14:41,360
<i>Hello, Qing Ye.</i>

135
00:14:41,360 --> 00:14:44,000
<i>I'm from Huanji Study Abroad.</i>

136
00:14:44,000 --> 00:14:46,200
<i>There's a situation with your application.</i>

137
00:14:46,200 --> 00:14:48,159
<i>You'd better come over right away.</i>

138
00:14:48,159 --> 00:14:50,440
<i>The school needs to see you now.</i>

139
00:14:50,440 --> 00:14:52,220
Okay, I'll be right there.

140
00:15:00,675 --> 00:15:02,879
Qing Ye, you are outstanding.

141
00:15:02,879 --> 00:15:06,280
But unfortunately,
the school cannot accept you.

142
00:15:06,280 --> 00:15:07,364
Why?

143
00:15:07,364 --> 00:15:11,247
[Anonymous Report]
We got an anonymous report about your family.

144
00:15:13,173 --> 00:15:14,519
Someone reported me?

145
00:15:14,519 --> 00:15:15,519
Yes.

146
00:15:15,519 --> 00:15:17,080
According to the report,

147
00:15:17,080 --> 00:15:21,200
you concealed your father's
alleged economic crimes and his frozen assets.

148
00:15:21,200 --> 00:15:22,360
Under these circumstances,

149
00:15:22,360 --> 00:15:24,387
the school has the right to revoke your offer.

150
00:15:24,387 --> 00:15:25,720
And for the next five years,

151
00:15:25,720 --> 00:15:28,840
you cannot apply to this school again.

152
00:15:28,840 --> 00:15:30,587
I'm truly sorry.

153
00:15:35,720 --> 00:15:36,960
Hello. This way, please.

154
00:15:37,555 --> 00:15:39,440
- Two avocado specials. Thank you.
- Here.

155
00:15:39,440 --> 00:15:40,900
Okay.

156
00:15:42,679 --> 00:15:43,919
Hello.

157
00:15:43,919 --> 00:15:45,080
When will you be here?

158
00:15:45,080 --> 00:15:47,725
I got you your favorite drink.

159
00:15:58,039 --> 00:15:59,762
Qing Ye.

160
00:15:59,762 --> 00:16:01,762
Why are you here?

161
00:16:03,080 --> 00:16:05,759
Meng Rui Hang asked me to come.

162
00:16:05,759 --> 00:16:07,519
Right. You're finally back in Beijing.

163
00:16:07,519 --> 00:16:10,240
We wanted to celebrate.

164
00:16:10,240 --> 00:16:11,440
Leaving the group chat,

165
00:16:11,440 --> 00:16:12,559
ignoring my messages,

166
00:16:12,559 --> 00:16:14,440
and blocking me.

167
00:16:14,440 --> 00:16:17,125
Is this your way of celebrating?

168
00:16:21,519 --> 00:16:23,537
You wrote that report, didn't you?

169
00:16:27,240 --> 00:16:29,280
Qing Ye, you're so smart.

170
00:16:29,280 --> 00:16:31,370
I knew you'd figure it out.

171
00:16:32,799 --> 00:16:37,720
All that talk about
letting me stay at your place.

172
00:16:37,720 --> 00:16:40,400
You didn't want me to come back at all.

173
00:16:42,879 --> 00:16:44,562
Why?

174
00:16:45,799 --> 00:16:47,937
Because you like Meng Rui Hang?

175
00:16:48,519 --> 00:16:50,559
So you knew all along.

176
00:16:50,559 --> 00:16:52,679
But you pretended not to notice.

177
00:16:52,679 --> 00:16:54,159
I like him,

178
00:16:54,159 --> 00:16:56,039
but he only has eyes for you.

179
00:16:56,039 --> 00:16:58,840
I wasn't pretending.

180
00:16:58,840 --> 00:17:01,373
I just wasn't interested at all.

181
00:17:02,279 --> 00:17:03,840
From today on,

182
00:17:03,840 --> 00:17:06,012
we are no longer friends.

183
00:17:06,640 --> 00:17:08,359
We were never real friends anyway.

184
00:17:08,359 --> 00:17:10,040
He Le Ling!

185
00:17:10,040 --> 00:17:11,702
Rui Hang.

186
00:17:14,440 --> 00:17:16,262
You've gone too far.

187
00:17:23,200 --> 00:17:24,800
Come in.

188
00:17:29,920 --> 00:17:31,119
Your slippers.

189
00:17:31,119 --> 00:17:32,875
Still the same ones.

190
00:17:33,720 --> 00:17:34,920
Thank you.

191
00:17:34,920 --> 00:17:36,825
It's nothing.

192
00:17:38,200 --> 00:17:41,240
Well, I won't stay for long.

193
00:17:41,240 --> 00:17:43,800
I'll leave as soon as I find a hotel.

194
00:17:43,800 --> 00:17:45,160
Quit being so polite.

195
00:17:45,160 --> 00:17:46,900
I'd never let you stay at a hotel.

196
00:17:46,900 --> 00:17:48,680
The housekeeper will get the guest room ready.

197
00:17:48,680 --> 00:17:50,487
Just stay here.

198
00:17:54,559 --> 00:17:56,559
Go on in.

199
00:17:56,559 --> 00:17:57,975
I'll take that.

200
00:18:09,400 --> 00:18:10,880
Ye.

201
00:18:10,880 --> 00:18:12,344
Auntie.

202
00:18:12,344 --> 00:18:13,425
Well...

203
00:18:13,425 --> 00:18:17,160
Mom, I want Qing Ye to stay with us
for a while.

204
00:18:19,320 --> 00:18:20,519
Of course.

205
00:18:20,519 --> 00:18:21,799
No big deal.

206
00:18:21,799 --> 00:18:24,119
Ye, come on, sit down.

207
00:18:24,119 --> 00:18:25,700
Sit here.

208
00:18:26,612 --> 00:18:29,559
How did you lose so much weight?

209
00:18:29,559 --> 00:18:31,837
Here, have some water.

210
00:18:32,440 --> 00:18:34,000
Thank you, Auntie.

211
00:18:34,000 --> 00:18:35,359
Don't mention it.

212
00:18:35,359 --> 00:18:37,039
Our families are so close.

213
00:18:37,039 --> 00:18:39,279
I've always treated you like my own daughter.

214
00:18:39,279 --> 00:18:41,625
Make yourself at home.

215
00:18:42,440 --> 00:18:43,640
Are you hungry?

216
00:18:43,640 --> 00:18:45,599
I'm not.

217
00:18:45,599 --> 00:18:46,880
Don't be so polite with me.

218
00:18:46,880 --> 00:18:48,839
I'll go wash some fruit for you.

219
00:18:48,839 --> 00:18:49,920
Drink some water.

220
00:18:49,920 --> 00:18:52,200
Hang Hang. Come and give me a hand.

221
00:18:52,200 --> 00:18:53,912
I'll head over there.

222
00:19:08,079 --> 00:19:09,279
You silly boy.

223
00:19:09,279 --> 00:19:12,000
Why didn't you tell me
you were bringing her back?

224
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:14,550
What's the matter?

225
00:19:14,550 --> 00:19:18,440
Your dad's company has done business
with theirs.

226
00:19:18,440 --> 00:19:21,640
Our family could easily get dragged in.

227
00:19:21,640 --> 00:19:23,160
At this point,

228
00:19:23,160 --> 00:19:25,760
everyone is cutting ties with them.

229
00:19:25,760 --> 00:19:28,279
Mom, what do you mean by that?

230
00:19:28,279 --> 00:19:31,187
Do we have to cut ties with her, too?

231
00:19:31,799 --> 00:19:34,039
What a naive child.

232
00:19:34,039 --> 00:19:36,119
I'm doing this for your own good.

233
00:19:36,119 --> 00:19:38,599
Do you want to end up homeless like her,

234
00:19:38,599 --> 00:19:41,975
living in some poor countryside?

235
00:19:41,975 --> 00:19:44,039
Qing Ye is in trouble, I have to help.

236
00:19:44,039 --> 00:19:47,250
Others might ignore this, but I can't.

237
00:19:47,250 --> 00:19:50,400
Silly boy, didn't you hear me?

238
00:19:50,400 --> 00:19:52,559
Anyway, I've made myself clear.

239
00:19:52,559 --> 00:19:55,225
Cut ties with her sooner.

240
00:19:59,440 --> 00:20:00,599
Ye.

241
00:20:00,599 --> 00:20:04,000
I washed your favorite cherries
and avocados for you.

242
00:20:04,000 --> 00:20:05,119
Where is she?

243
00:20:05,119 --> 00:20:06,520
Qing Ye?

244
00:20:06,520 --> 00:20:07,800
She left?

245
00:20:09,920 --> 00:20:11,373
Fine, let her go.

246
00:20:14,680 --> 00:20:17,599
<i>Sorry, the number you dialed is
temporarily unavailable.</i>

247
00:20:18,806 --> 00:20:19,920
What are you...

248
00:20:19,920 --> 00:20:21,319
Hang Hang!

249
00:20:21,319 --> 00:20:22,386
You...

250
00:20:23,559 --> 00:20:24,745
<i>Ye.</i>

251
00:20:24,745 --> 00:20:26,559
<i>Your father's situation</i>

252
00:20:26,559 --> 00:20:27,880
<i>is not very optimistic.</i>

253
00:20:28,640 --> 00:20:30,519
<i>The victims have filed a joint appeal.</i>

254
00:20:30,519 --> 00:20:33,240
<i>The evidence gathering and
investigation process are very complicated.</i>

255
00:20:33,240 --> 00:20:35,240
<i>Right now, everything is uncertain.</i>

256
00:20:36,039 --> 00:20:37,520
<i>But don't be too upset.</i>

257
00:20:37,520 --> 00:20:39,799
<i>The investigation is still ongoing.</i>

258
00:20:39,799 --> 00:20:42,000
<i>The legal team is doing their best</i>

259
00:20:42,000 --> 00:20:43,799
<i>to clear your father's name.</i>

260
00:20:43,799 --> 00:20:45,359
Is there a good chance?

261
00:20:45,359 --> 00:20:47,359
<i>No one can guarantee anything.</i>

262
00:20:47,359 --> 00:20:48,559
<i>Until the results are out,</i>

263
00:20:48,559 --> 00:20:50,333
<i>no one dares to promise anything.</i>

264
00:20:51,720 --> 00:20:52,960
I understand.

265
00:20:52,960 --> 00:20:54,880
<i>Are you back in Beijing?</i>

266
00:20:54,880 --> 00:20:56,279
<i>Where are you staying now?</i>

267
00:20:56,279 --> 00:20:58,039
<i>If you have nowhere to go, come to me.</i>

268
00:20:58,039 --> 00:20:59,559
No need, Uncle Sun.

269
00:20:59,559 --> 00:21:01,860
You've done enough for my family.

270
00:21:01,860 --> 00:21:03,099
<i>How about this?</i>

271
00:21:03,099 --> 00:21:04,839
<i>I'll send you some more money.</i>

272
00:21:04,839 --> 00:21:06,738
<i>Don't mistreat yourself.</i>

273
00:21:06,738 --> 00:21:08,400
Really, I'm good.

274
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:09,851
Thank you, Uncle Sun.

275
00:21:10,680 --> 00:21:12,110
I'll hang up now.

276
00:21:30,604 --> 00:21:31,928
[Unlock failed]
[Please try again]

277
00:22:12,259 --> 00:22:14,040
Ye, it's raining.

278
00:22:14,799 --> 00:22:17,172
We must put our hoods on.

279
00:22:17,172 --> 00:22:19,915
Otherwise, if we get wet, we'll catch a cold.

280
00:22:26,960 --> 00:22:28,165
Let's go.

281
00:24:07,920 --> 00:24:09,839
You haven't eaten all day, right?

282
00:24:09,839 --> 00:24:11,347
Just make do with this.

283
00:24:14,359 --> 00:24:16,200
If you don't want to eat,

284
00:24:16,200 --> 00:24:17,690
at least warm your hands with it.

285
00:24:27,440 --> 00:24:29,532
Why did you come to Beijing?

286
00:24:31,620 --> 00:24:33,564
Because I found...

287
00:24:33,564 --> 00:24:36,277
a loophole in our previous contract.

288
00:24:45,012 --> 00:24:46,318
It says here

289
00:24:46,318 --> 00:24:47,970
the expiration date

290
00:24:47,970 --> 00:24:49,720
[Temporary Residency Service Contract]
is the 10th.

291
00:24:49,720 --> 00:24:51,700
That means before the 10th,

292
00:24:51,700 --> 00:24:53,900
I must ensure your personal safety.

293
00:24:57,265 --> 00:24:59,298
Right now, until the 10th,

294
00:24:59,298 --> 00:25:01,012
there are still 15 minutes left.

295
00:25:04,366 --> 00:25:06,427
And after 15 minutes?

296
00:25:09,720 --> 00:25:11,759
If you're willing,

297
00:25:11,759 --> 00:25:14,098
you can come back to Zhazhating with me.

298
00:25:14,098 --> 00:25:15,950
My home is your home.

299
00:25:33,330 --> 00:25:35,160
Do you want to renew the contract?

300
00:25:35,160 --> 00:25:36,759
Effective immediately.

301
00:25:42,913 --> 00:25:44,151
Yes.

302
00:25:50,319 --> 00:25:51,706
But...

303
00:25:51,706 --> 00:25:53,119
before we go back,

304
00:25:53,119 --> 00:25:54,853
you have to come home with me first.

305
00:25:54,853 --> 00:25:56,433
You can't even get into your house.

306
00:25:56,433 --> 00:25:57,992
How are we supposed to go?

307
00:25:58,812 --> 00:26:00,018
Don't worry.

308
00:26:00,018 --> 00:26:01,427
I have a way.

309
00:26:11,059 --> 00:26:13,798
By the way, how did you know where I live?

310
00:26:13,798 --> 00:26:15,039
My mom told me.

311
00:26:15,039 --> 00:26:16,640
The front door access code
seems to have changed.

312
00:26:16,640 --> 00:26:18,052
Let's go through the back door.

313
00:26:18,052 --> 00:26:19,799
Why not the back door just now?

314
00:26:19,799 --> 00:26:21,421
I didn't think of it.

315
00:26:31,272 --> 00:26:32,966
This way, this way.

316
00:26:44,893 --> 00:26:47,465
These flowers are all dead.

317
00:26:48,246 --> 00:26:49,545
Yeah.

318
00:26:49,545 --> 00:26:50,992
Since my dad had his trouble,

319
00:26:50,992 --> 00:26:52,519
nobody's taken care of this place.

320
00:26:52,519 --> 00:26:54,159
They definitely couldn't survive.

321
00:26:54,159 --> 00:26:56,326
Did your mom grow all of these?

322
00:26:56,326 --> 00:26:58,083
She really loves gardening.

323
00:26:58,893 --> 00:27:01,733
I was thinking of taking two pots
back to Zhazhating.

324
00:27:01,733 --> 00:27:03,317
But that's out of the question now.

325
00:27:09,232 --> 00:27:11,692
Look. Is this one still alive?

326
00:27:12,458 --> 00:27:13,987
Let me see.

327
00:27:13,987 --> 00:27:15,607
It's green.

328
00:27:15,607 --> 00:27:18,640
Yeah. This one's alive. It's a Welwitschia.

329
00:27:18,640 --> 00:27:19,861
An orchid?

330
00:27:20,839 --> 00:27:22,702
This plant is incredibly tough.

331
00:27:22,702 --> 00:27:24,845
It can survive in the desert
for a long, long time.

332
00:27:24,845 --> 00:27:26,186
Easy to take care of.

333
00:27:26,186 --> 00:27:27,899
Perfect for taking back to Zhazhating.

334
00:27:29,932 --> 00:27:31,135
This one it is.

335
00:27:31,979 --> 00:27:33,253
Let's go inside.

336
00:27:42,366 --> 00:27:43,683
Come on, come on.

337
00:28:02,606 --> 00:28:03,759
Why is your house...

338
00:28:03,759 --> 00:28:05,180
Why is your house so cold?

339
00:28:05,180 --> 00:28:06,440
You don't know, do you?

340
00:28:06,440 --> 00:28:08,992
Central AC and ventilation system.

341
00:28:10,619 --> 00:28:12,368
Nothing beats the comfort of home.

342
00:28:37,673 --> 00:28:39,959
These trophies and certificates...

343
00:28:39,959 --> 00:28:41,485
Are they all yours?

344
00:28:42,440 --> 00:28:45,087
Back in school,
I entered all kinds of competitions?

345
00:28:50,860 --> 00:28:52,129
Wait.

346
00:28:56,873 --> 00:28:58,559
Xing Wu, Xing Wu!

347
00:28:58,559 --> 00:28:59,818
Quick, come here!

348
00:29:04,739 --> 00:29:06,018
Look.

349
00:29:07,365 --> 00:29:08,972
Let's finish all of these today.

350
00:29:08,972 --> 00:29:11,105
We won't get to eat them back in Zhazhating.

351
00:29:12,913 --> 00:29:14,232
Here, take it.

352
00:29:23,712 --> 00:29:25,386
How is it? Is it good?

353
00:29:26,106 --> 00:29:27,546
It's good.

354
00:29:29,439 --> 00:29:31,945
Well. Now try this flavor.

355
00:29:32,565 --> 00:29:34,228
I absolutely love this one.

356
00:29:35,039 --> 00:29:36,403
How is it?

357
00:29:36,403 --> 00:29:37,645
Is it good?

358
00:29:38,419 --> 00:29:39,893
This one's good too.

359
00:29:39,893 --> 00:29:41,304
Try this one.

360
00:29:44,551 --> 00:29:46,071
This is also delicious.

361
00:29:47,012 --> 00:29:48,392
Try the one I just had.

362
00:29:48,392 --> 00:29:50,101
It's my favorite flavor.

363
00:29:51,143 --> 00:29:52,200
Your favorite?

364
00:29:52,200 --> 00:29:53,476
What flavor is it?

365
00:29:54,119 --> 00:29:55,735
Cookies &amp; Cream Vanilla.

366
00:29:56,458 --> 00:29:59,007
- Is it good?
- Cookies &amp; Cream Vanilla.

367
00:30:00,873 --> 00:30:02,222
This is good.

368
00:30:03,857 --> 00:30:05,419
Welcome, Xing Wu,

369
00:30:05,419 --> 00:30:07,583
to Qing Ye's summer.

370
00:30:13,032 --> 00:30:14,711
Cheers.

371
00:30:14,711 --> 00:30:16,227
Cheers.

372
00:30:44,300 --> 00:30:45,847
Need a hand?

373
00:30:46,740 --> 00:30:48,782
Go to the bathroom.
Grab all my skincare products

374
00:30:48,782 --> 00:30:49,993
and toiletries.

375
00:30:49,993 --> 00:30:51,290
Okay.

376
00:30:59,841 --> 00:31:01,419
All here. Take a look.

377
00:31:01,419 --> 00:31:02,820
Let me see.

378
00:31:02,820 --> 00:31:04,300
Yes, that's everything.

379
00:31:04,300 --> 00:31:06,449
Okay.

380
00:31:10,820 --> 00:31:12,219
Xing Wu.

381
00:31:12,219 --> 00:31:14,060
I've had this piggy bank since I was little.

382
00:31:14,060 --> 00:31:15,259
It's gotta be full.

383
00:31:15,259 --> 00:31:18,189
Quick. Help me crack it open.

384
00:31:19,460 --> 00:31:20,780
Can I just smash it?

385
00:31:20,780 --> 00:31:22,866
Sure.

386
00:31:28,640 --> 00:31:31,079
Wow, that's a lot.

387
00:31:34,955 --> 00:31:36,419
There's more here.

388
00:31:36,419 --> 00:31:38,446
Give them to me.

389
00:31:40,419 --> 00:31:41,780
Put this on.

390
00:31:41,780 --> 00:31:43,019
Okay.

391
00:31:43,019 --> 00:31:44,100
The clothes?

392
00:31:44,100 --> 00:31:45,499
Put this on.

393
00:31:45,499 --> 00:31:47,060
Too thick, too much space.

394
00:31:47,060 --> 00:31:49,499
Hurry, hurry, hurry!

395
00:31:49,499 --> 00:31:52,058
Let's go, let's go, let's go!

396
00:31:52,900 --> 00:31:55,210
This way.

397
00:31:59,025 --> 00:32:00,855
- Who's there?
- Security!

398
00:32:00,855 --> 00:32:02,019
- Follow me. Follow me.
- Stop!

399
00:32:02,019 --> 00:32:03,620
This way, this way.

400
00:32:03,620 --> 00:32:04,820
What are you doing?

401
00:32:04,820 --> 00:32:07,340
Run! Run!

402
00:32:07,340 --> 00:32:10,060
Stop there! Stop right there!

403
00:32:10,060 --> 00:32:11,400
Run! Run!

404
00:32:11,400 --> 00:32:13,699
Wait for me! It's too dark. I can't see.

405
00:32:13,699 --> 00:32:16,252
You'll see when it gets light.

406
00:32:16,252 --> 00:32:18,080
Stop!

407
00:32:18,080 --> 00:32:20,640
Stop!

408
00:33:09,120 --> 00:33:11,659
- Oh my god!
- Wait, wait!

409
00:33:11,659 --> 00:33:14,591
It's spilling! It's spilling!

410
00:33:18,900 --> 00:33:19,979
Oh, man.

411
00:33:19,979 --> 00:33:22,100
Did... Did we...

412
00:33:22,100 --> 00:33:24,100
Did we lose them?

413
00:33:24,100 --> 00:33:26,419
Yes, we lost them.

414
00:33:26,419 --> 00:33:28,694
No one in sight.

415
00:33:29,699 --> 00:33:30,979
Why were we running?

416
00:33:30,979 --> 00:33:32,419
The security guard chased me,

417
00:33:32,419 --> 00:33:34,603
so I ran.

418
00:33:43,280 --> 00:33:45,664
The sun is coming up.

419
00:33:52,320 --> 00:33:54,120
Thank you.

420
00:33:54,120 --> 00:33:55,861
Xing Wu.

421
00:33:59,800 --> 00:34:01,979
A new day has begun.

422
00:34:01,979 --> 00:34:04,267
Come home with me.

423
00:34:10,139 --> 00:34:13,742
But I want to go somewhere first.

424
00:34:16,360 --> 00:34:18,459
Let's go.

425
00:34:18,459 --> 00:34:20,725
Let's go.

426
00:34:36,459 --> 00:34:37,740
Mom.

427
00:34:37,740 --> 00:34:39,419
I'm here to see you.

428
00:34:39,419 --> 00:34:41,780
I brought you your favorite Coke,
[Tomb of Wife Lin Wanxin]

429
00:34:41,780 --> 00:34:45,013
and the daisies you like.

430
00:34:46,840 --> 00:34:51,300
Mom. I've been through a lot lately.

431
00:34:51,300 --> 00:34:53,860
I thought

432
00:34:53,860 --> 00:34:56,099
falling from the peak to rock bottom

433
00:34:56,099 --> 00:34:58,369
was bad enough.

434
00:34:59,139 --> 00:35:01,180
I didn't expect

435
00:35:01,180 --> 00:35:03,700
I'd fall from rock bottom

436
00:35:03,700 --> 00:35:06,678
even further into the abyss.

437
00:35:09,419 --> 00:35:10,459
But

438
00:35:10,459 --> 00:35:12,805
you don't have to worry anymore.

439
00:35:13,560 --> 00:35:16,700
When I was at my most desperate,

440
00:35:16,700 --> 00:35:19,740
someone reached out to help me.

441
00:35:19,740 --> 00:35:21,619
Do you remember him?

442
00:35:21,619 --> 00:35:24,560
My cousin from Auntie's, Xing Wu.

443
00:35:24,560 --> 00:35:27,440
You probably haven't seen him for a long time.

444
00:35:27,440 --> 00:35:28,680
This time,

445
00:35:28,680 --> 00:35:31,846
he came to Beijing just to get me.

446
00:35:37,019 --> 00:35:39,077
Hello.

447
00:35:39,891 --> 00:35:41,740
In front of you,

448
00:35:41,740 --> 00:35:44,019
I can't tell any lies.

449
00:35:44,019 --> 00:35:46,740
I was indeed worried about Qing Ye.

450
00:35:46,740 --> 00:35:49,160
That's why I came to Beijing.

451
00:35:49,160 --> 00:35:51,846
But actually,

452
00:35:52,560 --> 00:35:54,266
I...

453
00:35:54,266 --> 00:35:56,660
I can't say

454
00:35:56,660 --> 00:35:59,922
I came to Beijing solely for her.

455
00:36:01,520 --> 00:36:03,852
Then why did you come?

456
00:36:12,400 --> 00:36:15,880
This one is our top-of-the-line model,
and also the latest one.

457
00:36:15,880 --> 00:36:18,619
It's waterproof, anti-corrosive, and foldable.

458
00:36:18,619 --> 00:36:20,271
You really came to the right place today.

459
00:36:20,271 --> 00:36:23,419
Right now, only our offline stores
can provide such custom service.

460
00:36:23,419 --> 00:36:26,619
And right now, we have a promotion in-store.

461
00:36:26,619 --> 00:36:27,780
I'll take this one then.

462
00:36:27,780 --> 00:36:29,120
Sure, no problem.

463
00:36:29,120 --> 00:36:30,160
Do you have a new one in stock?

464
00:36:30,160 --> 00:36:33,074
Yes, we do. Please follow me.

465
00:36:34,579 --> 00:36:37,260
The original price of this wheelchair is
7,999 yuan.

466
00:36:37,260 --> 00:36:39,131
Since we have a promotion today,

467
00:36:39,131 --> 00:36:41,340
after the discount,

468
00:36:41,340 --> 00:36:42,539
it's 6,999 yuan.

469
00:36:42,539 --> 00:36:44,300
How would you like to pay?

470
00:36:44,300 --> 00:36:45,640
Cash.

471
00:36:45,640 --> 00:36:47,900
Okay.

472
00:36:47,900 --> 00:36:49,419
Here is 6,800 yuan.

473
00:36:49,419 --> 00:36:50,419
I still owe 200.

474
00:36:50,419 --> 00:36:51,521
Can I pay with a QR code?

475
00:36:51,521 --> 00:36:53,000
Yes, that works.

476
00:36:53,000 --> 00:36:55,263
Don't bother.

477
00:36:57,937 --> 00:36:59,360
It's for Grandma's wheelchair.

478
00:36:59,360 --> 00:37:01,524
I want to help out too.

479
00:37:16,680 --> 00:37:19,562
[Zhazhating]

480
00:37:23,440 --> 00:37:26,625
Zhazhating still smells the same.

481
00:37:29,539 --> 00:37:31,820
You're gonna have to get used to this place.

482
00:37:31,820 --> 00:37:33,200
Who says I'm not used to it?

483
00:37:33,200 --> 00:37:35,416
It's the smell of the sea.

484
00:37:36,099 --> 00:37:37,200
Everyone will be so happy

485
00:37:37,200 --> 00:37:39,700
to see you back.

486
00:37:39,700 --> 00:37:41,860
Who was it that told me

487
00:37:41,860 --> 00:37:44,820
to leave as soon as possible
and never come back?

488
00:37:44,820 --> 00:37:46,860
I only said that because I hoped
your family was okay,

489
00:37:46,860 --> 00:37:48,440
so you could leave here as soon as possible.

490
00:37:48,440 --> 00:37:51,059
Xing Wu. When did you get a cousin?

491
00:37:51,059 --> 00:37:52,260
I've given this girl a ride before.

492
00:37:52,260 --> 00:37:53,900
I never heard your mom mention her.

493
00:37:53,900 --> 00:37:56,848
I picked her up on the streets of Beijing.

494
00:37:59,120 --> 00:38:01,157
We're here.

495
00:38:14,915 --> 00:38:16,120
Welwitschia.

496
00:38:16,120 --> 00:38:19,180
It's a plant native to the desert.

497
00:38:19,180 --> 00:38:20,660
Xing Wu.

498
00:38:20,660 --> 00:38:22,340
Before I left, you said

499
00:38:22,340 --> 00:38:25,220
that roses couldn't bloom in a barren desert.

500
00:38:25,220 --> 00:38:27,300
That's true.

501
00:38:27,300 --> 00:38:28,660
But,

502
00:38:28,660 --> 00:38:31,539
weak grass doesn't grow in the desert either.

503
00:38:31,539 --> 00:38:34,180
If you can survive the worst,

504
00:38:34,180 --> 00:38:37,480
nature's got your back as the fittest.

505
00:38:37,480 --> 00:38:41,190
Zhazhating, I'm back.

506
00:38:44,520 --> 00:38:46,690
Ye?

507
00:38:48,459 --> 00:38:50,419
Are you

508
00:38:50,419 --> 00:38:52,180
back?

509
00:38:52,180 --> 00:38:54,315
Auntie.

510
00:39:12,040 --> 00:39:16,131
[Xuan Island Barbershop]

511
00:39:19,059 --> 00:39:22,019
Auntie. This silk scarf is for you. Try it on.

512
00:39:22,019 --> 00:39:23,419
For me?

513
00:39:23,419 --> 00:39:26,059
I know this brand.

514
00:39:26,059 --> 00:39:28,099
Designer goods really are different.

515
00:39:28,099 --> 00:39:29,579
What a texture.

516
00:39:29,579 --> 00:39:32,300
It's so smooth and silky.

517
00:39:32,300 --> 00:39:33,619
And these skincare products

518
00:39:33,619 --> 00:39:34,619
are for you too.

519
00:39:34,619 --> 00:39:36,740
It's windy by the sea.
Don't forget to moisturize.

520
00:39:36,740 --> 00:39:38,242
Are these all for me?

521
00:39:38,242 --> 00:39:41,059
They must have been very expensive.

522
00:39:41,059 --> 00:39:42,600
As long as you like them, Auntie.

523
00:39:42,600 --> 00:39:44,539
I love them!

524
00:39:44,539 --> 00:39:46,660
Grandma, this is the power switch.

525
00:39:46,660 --> 00:39:48,340
Once you turn it on,

526
00:39:48,340 --> 00:39:50,660
this lever is for forward and reverse,

527
00:39:50,660 --> 00:39:52,099
and this is for steering left and right.

528
00:39:52,099 --> 00:39:56,019
From now on, you can use this
to go have coffee with Grandma Zhao.

529
00:39:56,019 --> 00:39:57,860
Wonderful.

530
00:39:57,860 --> 00:39:58,979
And look.

531
00:39:58,979 --> 00:40:01,499
This is a souvenir badge of Tian'anmen.

532
00:40:01,499 --> 00:40:04,099
Qing Ye bought it especially for you.

533
00:40:04,099 --> 00:40:06,139
It's so beautiful.

534
00:40:06,139 --> 00:40:07,499
Wu, Ye,

535
00:40:07,499 --> 00:40:10,625
you're both so thoughtful.

536
00:40:11,459 --> 00:40:13,579
Look at me. I was so busy looking at the gifts.

537
00:40:13,579 --> 00:40:14,700
I forgot to ask.

538
00:40:14,700 --> 00:40:17,346
Why are you back?

539
00:40:21,590 --> 00:40:22,643
There was a change of plans.

540
00:40:22,643 --> 00:40:24,260
I'm not going abroad for the time being.

541
00:40:24,260 --> 00:40:25,997
- You're not going abroad?
- No.

542
00:40:25,997 --> 00:40:27,226
That's good news.

543
00:40:27,226 --> 00:40:28,914
I don't know if it's

544
00:40:28,914 --> 00:40:33,092
gold on the streets or cash in the air.

545
00:40:33,092 --> 00:40:35,440
Everyone is scrambling to get overseas.

546
00:40:35,440 --> 00:40:38,061
It's okay to stay. Life here is good.

547
00:40:38,061 --> 00:40:41,039
Auntie, you're right. I think so too.

548
00:40:41,039 --> 00:40:42,679
So I might

549
00:40:42,679 --> 00:40:46,280
have to live here for a bit longer.

550
00:40:46,280 --> 00:40:47,840
Sure, that's fine.

551
00:40:47,840 --> 00:40:49,960
Ye, you can stay here

552
00:40:49,960 --> 00:40:52,210
as long as you like.

553
00:40:52,210 --> 00:40:53,239
So

554
00:40:53,239 --> 00:40:56,045
how long are you going to stay?

555
00:40:59,159 --> 00:41:00,440
A year.

556
00:41:00,440 --> 00:41:02,320
A year?

557
00:41:02,320 --> 00:41:04,351
Or maybe two years.

558
00:41:07,519 --> 00:41:09,280
Come out.

559
00:41:09,280 --> 00:41:11,702
I have something to tell you.

560
00:41:12,760 --> 00:41:14,541
Come on, come on.

561
00:41:15,360 --> 00:41:18,034
Come with me.

562
00:41:24,000 --> 00:41:25,679
Go ahead.

563
00:41:25,679 --> 00:41:28,966
- What's going on?
- Keep your voice down.

564
00:41:33,760 --> 00:41:35,840
Ye.

565
00:41:35,840 --> 00:41:37,000
Don't worry.

566
00:41:37,000 --> 00:41:39,119
It's okay.

567
00:41:39,119 --> 00:41:40,639
Wu will handle

568
00:41:40,639 --> 00:41:43,039
your auntie.

569
00:41:43,039 --> 00:41:46,140
You just stay here as long as you want.

570
00:41:53,640 --> 00:41:55,360
I really feel for her.

571
00:41:55,360 --> 00:41:56,960
Her family's in a huge mess.

572
00:41:56,960 --> 00:41:59,960
She packed just a few things.
And she almost got caught by security.

573
00:41:59,960 --> 00:42:01,055
Plus,

574
00:42:01,055 --> 00:42:03,159
she can't go abroad.

575
00:42:03,159 --> 00:42:06,280
Her friends in Beijing can't help her now.

576
00:42:06,280 --> 00:42:08,639
Although we're not related by blood,

577
00:42:08,639 --> 00:42:11,079
we should help her out.

578
00:42:11,079 --> 00:42:12,674
Right?

579
00:42:13,280 --> 00:42:16,239
Why does that
sounds so familiar?

580
00:42:16,239 --> 00:42:18,159
You said it.

581
00:42:18,159 --> 00:42:20,707
So you took it to heart?

582
00:42:23,199 --> 00:42:25,360
But Mr. Sun is really something.

583
00:42:25,360 --> 00:42:28,559
Why didn't he contact me in advance?

584
00:42:28,559 --> 00:42:31,639
He should've told me what was happening.

585
00:42:31,639 --> 00:42:33,159
I'll call and ask him.

586
00:42:33,159 --> 00:42:34,400
- Come back here.
- I...

587
00:42:34,400 --> 00:42:36,760
- What are you going to ask?
- He still owes me twenty thousand.

588
00:42:36,760 --> 00:42:38,199
I need to know what's going on.

589
00:42:38,199 --> 00:42:42,107
All her family's accounts are frozen.
You're not getting that money.

590
00:42:42,107 --> 00:42:44,000
Uncle Sun is just an employee of her dad's.

591
00:42:44,000 --> 00:42:45,679
There's no reason to ask him for money.

592
00:42:45,679 --> 00:42:48,237
So you're saying

593
00:42:48,880 --> 00:42:50,880
the money is gone,

594
00:42:50,880 --> 00:42:53,079
and we'll have to cover her expenses?

595
00:42:53,079 --> 00:42:54,199
Yes.

596
00:42:54,199 --> 00:42:56,936
Look, I can forget about that money.
But have you thought about this?

597
00:42:56,936 --> 00:42:58,463
She's not

598
00:42:58,463 --> 00:43:02,024
staying here for one or two months.
It's one or two years.

599
00:43:02,024 --> 00:43:04,039
What about her living expenses, tuition,

600
00:43:04,039 --> 00:43:06,519
and all the everyday stuff
like eating and clothes?

601
00:43:06,519 --> 00:43:08,460
Didn't she give you 30,000 yuan?

602
00:43:08,460 --> 00:43:09,525
But I already...

603
00:43:09,525 --> 00:43:14,960
Well, you know that.
I used that money to pay my debts.

604
00:43:14,960 --> 00:43:16,720
It's nearly the end of the month.

605
00:43:16,720 --> 00:43:18,760
I was banking on that 20,000 yuan
to knock off a bit more debt.

606
00:43:18,760 --> 00:43:20,814
So what now?

607
00:43:21,679 --> 00:43:23,559
Alright, alright.

608
00:43:23,559 --> 00:43:25,675
I'll handle it.

609
00:43:27,639 --> 00:43:29,639
Smile.

610
00:43:29,639 --> 00:43:31,784
I can't smile.

611
00:43:34,679 --> 00:43:37,362
You hear me? I can't smile.

